indication: 1.1 Plaque Psoriasis. TALTZ. Â®. is indicated for the treatment of patients 6 years of age and older with moderate-to-severe plaque psoriasis who are candidates for systemic therapy or phototherapy.
1.2 Psoriatic Arthritis. TALTZ is indicated for the treatment of adult patients with active psoriatic arthritis.
1.3 Ankylosing Spondylitis. TALTZ is indicated for the treatment of adult patients with active ankylosing spondylitis.

icd10_codes.description: Ankylosing spondylitis sacral and sacrococcygeal region

indication: 1.4 Non-radiographic Axial Spondyloarthritis. TALTZ is indicated for the treatment of adult patients with active non-radiographic axial spondyloarthritis (nr-axSpA) with objective signs of inflammation.
